CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 1, 1961, pg. A16, reads: "Mrs. Wynn Entertains - Mrs. Samuel J. Wynn, who was made a lifetime honorary member of the board of directors of the YWCA last week, entertained Saturday in her charming Iowa St. home in honor of retiring 'Y' executive, Miss Goldie Carter. A heap of prettily wrapped gifts, pleasant fellowship, and a delightful afternoon helped speed the popular Miss Carter on her way to Denver, Colo., where she will make her home with her sister.  Seated, left to right, at the head of the table, the hostess, Mrs. Wynn; Mmes. Anita Bolden Fitts, Moses Haze, Herbert E. Simmons, Homer S. Brown, Miss Carter; Mmes. R. L. Vann, James A. Jordon, Florence Kaufman.  Standing from left: Mmes. Murrel Wynn Jones, Cornell Talley, B. B. Corson, Miss Miriam Morritt, Mmes. Nathaniel Dandridge, Nathan Page, Harry W. Fulton, Raymond A. Walls. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait seated from left: Mrs. Samuel Wynn, Anita Bolden Fitts, Mrs. Moses Haze, Mrs. Herbert E. Simmons, Wilhelmina Byrd Brown, Ms. Carter, Jessie Vann, Marion Bond Jordon, Florence Kaufman; standing: Murrel Wynn Jones, Martha Talley, Mrs. B. B.
